entries.femaleVariant: How'd you even get involved in this mess?
This camp far?
How the hell'd you land in this mess?
I liked the color. The air freshener and booster seat came extra.
You know I don't mean the car.
What am I supposed to tell you? That I'm not about to let my partner rob me and get away with it? That my fixer made me look like a goddamned fool?
So why didn't she tell me she knew about Nash?
OK, we're almost there. We'll gather my guys, then ride to Rocky Ridge.
Rogue? Do better not to worry what her agenda might be.
entries.maleVariant: Rogue? Do better not to wonder what her agenda might be.

entries.femaleVariant: Goddamn, I can't stand the bitch!
Screw Rogue.
You'll have to ask her about Nash.
Know what? Screw Rogue. Can't see why you even care.
'Cause I need the money?
Don't let her push you around. She's not the only fixer in town.
Guess you'll have to ask her yourself.
You don't know her. Not at all.
Did she tell you she was the one to bring me and Nash together? Did she tell you it slipped her mind to mention Nash was Raffen Shiv?
Might not've known.
Rogue must've had her reasons.
Nash is Raffen Shiv?
Oh, I'll be sure to. I'll especially ask why she told me to work with Nash, yet forgot to mention he was Raffen.
Wait, Nash is Raffen?
Might not've known that side of him.
Must've had her reasons.
Rogue's a frigid old bitch. That's the truth.
But seriously – you didn't realize Nash was Raffen?
Yes, mostly. Nomads don't banish their own without a reason. So think – murderers, rapists, freaks.
Shit.
And that bitch had me working with scum like that.
I see you know things.
Don't you keep track of who's in the area? The Wraiths, right?
No. The sneak forgot to show me his Shiv card.
Don't make me laugh. A fixer of her standing knows. And Rogue probably knows we're talking about her right now!
Nash and I had a role to play in her game, her plan. That's it.
You don't say.
What about you? Why do you need that clown from the AV?
This particular clown's got intel I need. And I'm running out of time to get it.
Rogue might just like pulling strings.
Rogue’s queen of the Afterlife. Plays her pawns as she pleases.
Did you just call me a pawn?
Well, I think she's a lying, manipulative bitch. She put me together with that Raffen – did you know that?
Until now, they mostly jumped corporate transporters down by Highway Sixty-Four.
Yes... He runs with the Wraiths, the largest Raffen group in the area. You know about them, right?
Mhm. Nomads tossed out of clans.
How far's the camp?
Just past the city line. We'll jump on the Nine and head east.
Rogue won't open her mouth without weighing the for and against. What to spill and what to withhold.
Rode with the Bakker clan. Long time ago, that was.
Well, we have something in common after all.
They gather in teams, sometimes form actual gangs. Most of them are wanted and have warrants on their heads.
Yet… you're only here because she sent you.
But I'm not the one bitching about her.
I got a good look at 'er.
She rose to the top 'cause she reads people. So what if she keeps things to herself? It's a skill in her profession.
Nice ride. Lots of space. Practical.
Say no more. Please.
Nice ride.
Where'd you get this car?
Where'd you get the ride? Straight outta some driveway in Rancho?
Yes, exactly.
Is that a problem?
For me? No, not at all. I mean, there's no accounting for taste.
Screw you.
Rogue must've had her reasons.
Nash is Raffen Shiv?
But seriously – didn't realize Nash was Raffen?
No. The sneak forgot to show me his Shiv card.
Don't you keep track of who's in the area? The Wraiths, right?
Until now, they mostly jumped corporate transporters down by Highway Sixty-Four.
I see you know things.
Nomad blood.
